HEADWORD: Ichthyoidal
<hw>Ich`thy*oid"al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/: <grk>'ichqy`s</grk>,
<grk>-y`os</grk>, a fish + <grk>e'i^dos</grk> form.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Somewhat like a fish; having some of the
characteristics of fishes; -- said of some amphibians.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ichthyol</ent>⟦br⟧
